cs.CL, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.IR, cs.NE 

The paper discusses the development of methods for automatically detecting humorous statements, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language). Additionally, the paper mentions the use of Deep Learning, which suggests that it could also belong to cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning). The paper also involves ranking statements on a continuous scale, which could fall under cs.IR (Information Retrieval). Finally, the use of language models and neural networks suggests that it could also belong to cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing).
